The diagnostics and treatment of the chronic pancreatitis, complicated by ascitis. The analysis of diagnostic and treatment principles of the pancreatogenic ascitis was performed, using data of 26 patients. The diagnosis was revealed after the diagnostic laparoscopy and external drainage in 12 patients 14 patients were diagnosed with the help of the multispiral computed tomography. The combination of external pancreatogenic ascitis draining and local non-anatomic resection of the pancreas allowed better results.